The paper focuses on the problem of predicting human actions and intent in the context of human-robot cooperation, which is a key area of research in robotics (cs.RO). The approach is based on neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the importance of understanding human non-verbal cues, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical implications of predicting multiple action sequences, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
